      • setReadOnly

        public void setReadOnly(Any readOnly)
        Marks the file or directory named by this abstract pathname so that only read operations are allowed. Although written to be a property for the purposes of the Inq language, because of the underlying JDK File methods it can only be set true. Trying to set false generates a runtime exception.
